\frac{\sin(x)}{\cot(x)} + \cos(x) = \sec(x)
\cos(x)
\frac{\sin}{\cot}+\cos =\frac{\sin}{\frac{\cos}{\sin}}+\cos = \frac{\sin^2}{\cos} + \cos = \frac{\overbrace{\sin^2+\cos^2}^{=1}}{\cos} = \frac{1}{\cos} = \sec
\frac{\sin x}{\cot x}+\cos x=\frac{\sin x+\cos x\cot x}{\cot x} =\frac{\sin x+\cos x\cdot \displaystyle\frac{\cos x}{\sin x}}{\cot x}=
=\frac{\displaystyle\frac{\sin^2x+\cos^2x }{\sin x}}{\cot x}=\frac{1}{\sin x}\cdot \frac{1}{\cot x}=\frac{1}{\sin x}\cdot \frac{\sin x}{\cos x}=\frac{1}{\cos x}=\sec x. 
 \frac{\sin x}{\cot x}+\cos x=\sec x.
